description:
My place is good for solo adventurers, business travelers, and couples. It is conveniently located close to the A, C, and 1 Trains, New York Presbyterian Hospital, Columbia University Medical Center, Bank of America, various groceries, many restaurants, and the George Washington Bridge. The place is fully furnished. The studio is very clean as smoking and pets are not allowed.

Yes
house_rules:
• Check in time is 3PM - 6PM
• May not be safe or suitable for children (0-12 years)
• No parties or events
• Not suitable for pets
• No smoking
name: Your Home in The Heights

photos.caption: Welcome to your home in the heights, in a safe and quiet environment.
Washington Heights is the setting for the Broadway Play IN THE HEIGHTS written by Lin Manuel Miranda who also wrote the very popular HAMILTON.
Floating vintage luggage shelf for light things - keys, wallet, glasses
Full length mirror at the entryway - Smile for a selfie!
Message board and blinds which roll up or down depending on your preference
Kitchen with stove and single cup coffee maker
Cupboard - ground coffee, coffee filters, teas, sweetener
Bathroom entryway with towels, toilet paper, and hair dryer
Complimentary shampoo, conditioner, and body wash

review.comments: Хорошее соотношение цена-качество.Близко к метро,но до центра 30-50 минут.Для двоих человек ,не более.Рядом супермаркет.Нам показалось неудобным,что в первый день ключи мы забирали в кей- кафе до которого пришлось ехать с чемоданами после одиннадцати часового перелёта .
